                <head>No. 339.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L. S. Sackville West</persName> to
                        Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 17, 1887</date>. (Received May
                        18.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my note of the 25th ultimo and
                    to your reply of the 7th instant, I have the honor to inform you that Her
                    Majesty’s Government intimate that the intending emigrants are not paupers, but
                    crofters, whose passages are only partly paid from public funds, and that Her
                    Majesty’s Government would be glad to know whether this affects in any way the
                    tenor of your above-mentioned note.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">L. S. Sackville West.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
